description:
Job Duties:


Follow up cargoes;
Prepare purchases & sales contracts;
Co-ordinate with suppliers, buyers & head office to arrange loading schedules;
Handle full set shipping documents & issue invoices, etc.
Fulfill other duties related to operations;

 
Requirement:


University graduate in Shipping Logistics and Global Supply Chain are highly preferred;

Proficiency in Mandarin, English and Chinese;
Self-motivated, Reliable, Independent, Team work, Detail-minded and able to work under pressure;
1 to 2 years working experience in operations and logistics;

Fresh graduate will be also considered;
Immediately Available.

*Interested parties, please send full resume with current & expected salary & date available in MS WORD FORMAT ONLY to email:  jobs@HKETERNITY. com    or fax to 3527 0634

Hotline: (852) 3542 5082

For more jobs, please visit our website: www.hketernity.com

We are welcome applicants resend resumes to us even you have applied jobs in our company before.

(Personal data submitted are for recruitment purpose only.)

A multinational consumer goods company with global presence is looking for an Associate Director to join their logistics & operations team. The successful candidate will lead a sizable team in customer service, logistics and operation functions. 

The Position
This position will oversee the company's e-commerce, retail business operations and logistics functions. The successful candidate will partner with major stakeholders within all functional departments to drive business growth and enhance customer experience by offering best platforms from online to offline.


Managing the performance of 3PL to ensure all KPIs are met;
Explore new ways and best practices to reduce costs, improve service quality and reduce operational risk;
Manage the execution and completion of the defined project plans/ roadmaps through effectively coordinating people and resources that support annual business, financial and growth objectives;
Support business opportunities in compliance with global operational strategies. 

Requirement


Bachelor degree or above in supply chain, operations or any related discipline;
Minimum 10 years of managerial experience in which 5 years’ experience in logistics and customer service field;
Experience in O2O operation and leading service team;
Being proactive with strong interpersonal skills to communicate with different customers and colleagues;
Strong leadership with strategical thinking to achieve operational and customer service excellence.

 (All personal data collected will be kept confidential and is for recruitment purpose only.)

About Zeek
Zeek is the brand name under Kin Shun Information Technology Limited which incorporated in 2019. Zeek aims to provide smart logistics, SaaS solutions and online / offline integrated instant delivery service for Hong Kong and Southeast Asia market, meeting their needs for food & parcel delivery and last-mile logistics.

We strive for building an excellent delivery experience by adopting big data and artificial intelligence. With existing business in Hong Kong, Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand and Vietnam, we will continue to expand our business to Southeast Asia countries and regions like Taiwan, Philippines and Indonesia in near future.


Responsibilities:


To supervise and managing the delivery operations, particularly on workforce management strictly on company regulation to ensure the operations flow is smoothly and efficiency;
Oversees the strategy , planning .and execution of projects to  ensure accuracy  and cost-efficiency;
Experience with sortation center/ parcel fulfillment center, cost benefit analysis, labor productivity analysis in order to effectively plan and scheduling the operations resources in order to meet and exceed internal and external services levels at all times with productive and cost efficiency;
Work with related departments to maintain and enhance the platform of reward system for member activation and engagement;
Measure performance, provide a feedback as well as taking proactive steps to ensure the best practices are shared across all departments;
Create a positive and collaborative team environment by setting and regularly reviewing the achievement of team goals;
Document and track any failures/error including reporting on failure rates, causes, and preventable incidents;
Assist in training and coaching new and existing team members;
Perform ad-hoc duties / projects assigned by top management

Requirements:

Diploma holder or above in Logistics, Supply Chain Management or related disciplines;
5-7 years’ relevant experience of which 2 years were at supervisory level in operations from logistics/supply chain industries;
Experience in emerging technology in logistics and supply chain, including but not limited to open-platform, dynamic pricing; knowledge of cloud service in logistics is a plus;
Strong planning and analytical skills. Sensitive to numbers;
Good people management and presentation skills;
Independent, flexible, stress resistant and able to work in a fast pace team-base environment;
Proficiency in MS Excel, Word, PowerPoint and Chinese word processing;
Good command of both written and spoken English, Chinese and Putonghua

We offer competitive remuneration, birthday and work anniversary holidays and benefit packages to the right candidate.

Please send your detailed resume, with last and expected salary to our Human Resources Department by clicking "Apply Now”. 

(All information collected will be treated in strict confidence and used solely for recruitment)

Job Responsibilities:

1. Check and manage warehouse accounts, and check with the internal financial department to ensure that the accounts are clear;
2. Confirm customer requirements and provide the most reasonable air transportation plan;
3. Maintain good communication with suppliers and customers to ensure smooth cargo transportation;
4. Prepare quotations, documents, customs declarations and other documents;
5. Complete the on-site inspection work;
6. Other tasks assigned by the department.


 Job Requirements:

1. Priority is given to those with experience in logistics operations such as shipping and air transportation;
2. Those who are interested in freight, welcome fresh graduates;
3. Good execution, communication skills and teamwork spirit;
4. Language ability: English/Cantonese/Mandarin. Mastery: good;
5. Basic computer knowledge, familiar with Microsoft software operation;
6. Recognize the culture of Chinese-funded companies.

About Zeek
Zeek is the brand name under Kin Shun Information Technology Limited which incorporated in 2019. Zeek aims to provide smart logistics, SaaS solutions and online / offline integrated instant delivery service for Hong Kong and Southeast Asia market, meeting their needs for food & parcel delivery and last-mile logistics.

We strive for building an excellent delivery experience by adopting big data and artificial intelligence. With existing business in Hong Kong, Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand and Vietnam, we will continue to expand our business to Southeast Asia countries and regions like Taiwan, Philippines and Indonesia in near future.

Responsibilities: 

Represent headquarter to oversee operational and financial KPIs of Food & Quick Commerce business across multiple SEA markets, and provide executional inputs to local operations teams in optimizing operational efficiency and service level
Take lead in operational planning for launch of new markets or services in existing markets;
Maintain right sets of indicators and reports for effective analysis on services and operations, and also identifying improvement opportunities for Hong Kong and overseas markets;
Facilitate local operations team to diagnose existing issues in operations and the execution of initiatives by cooperating with various internal parties and external partners;
Take ownership on urgent issues in operations and take timely actions;
Keep abreast of the market’s leading practices and understand competitors’ operating models to ensure company’s practice has its competitive advantages;
Share knowledge and leading practices in operations in Headquarter for local operations teams to take reference;
Develop standard operating procedures and guidelines for overseas markets;
Develop BI report templates for operations management and monitoring across markets;
Perform ad-hoc duties assigned by Management

Requirements:

Degree holder in any disciplines; 
Minimum 4 years of experience in operations management, project management or consulting, with experiences in start-ups, logistic platforms, F&B or e-commerce sectors preferred;
Strong planning and analytical skills with strong business sense and problem-solving skill;
Sensitive to numbers and capable in scientific analysis, candidates with BI reporting experience have advantage;
Proactive and able to work under pressure with multi-tasking ability;
Independent, self-motivated, detail-oriented, good team player and able to work in a fast paced and dynamic working environment;
Good command of written and spoken English, Cantonese and Mandarin;
Proficient in MS applications, e.g. PowerPoint, Excel and Word

We offer competitive remuneration, birthday and work anniversary holidays and benefit packages to the right candidate.

Please send your detailed resume, with last and expected salary to our Human Resources Department by clicking "Apply Now”.  

(All information collected will be treated in strict confidence and used solely for recruitment)
